YENAGOA – Governor Seriake Dick­son of Bayelsa State has congratulated Governor Okezie Ikpeazu of Abia State and his Delta State counterpart, Ifeanyi Okowa, on the Supreme Court judgment affirming their elections. Dickson, the outgoing Chairman of the PDP Gov­ernors’ Forum, felicitated with the two governors in a statement on Thursday signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Fidelis Soriwei. He said the judgment of the apex court would give the expected relief to the governors to focus on gov­ernance. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Dickson pointed out that with the final resolution of the electoral dispute in their favour, Ikpeazu and Okowa would now concen­trate on delivering the div­idends of democracy to the people of their respective states. The governor com­mended the Supreme Court for the bold decision to affirm the mandates of the people of Delta and Abia states.